category: A SUCCESSFUL OPERATION
category comment: 

clue: Pliny the Elder mentions Scipio Africanus was born through this surgical delivery method

response: a Caesarean section

clue: For nerve injuries, a transplant surgery uses this technique that shares its name with a horticultural one

response: grafting

clue: Swann-Morton notes that the No. 10 size of this surgical tool is used "for making varying sizes of incision in skin"

response: a scalpel

clue: While a mastectomy removes the whole breast, this surgery takes out the cancerous cells & conserves part of the breast

response: a lumpectomy

clue: Part of biliary surgery, the operation to remove this, now one of the most common, was first done by Dr. Langenbuch in 1882

response: the gallbladder

